50|$|Millett LJ allowed Mothew's appeal, {{and held}} that a causal link needed to be established. Just because the {{solicitor}} himself had fiduciary duties to his clients, that {{did not mean that}} every <b>breach</b> <b>of</b> duty of care was a <b>breach</b> <b>of</b> a fiduciary duty. When considering <b>breaches</b> <b>of</b> <b>trust,</b> causation need not be demonstrated, since these are concerned with acts of bad faith or <b>breaches</b> <b>of</b> the duty of loyalty that result in restitutionary damages. The building society had been fully informed and had consented to Mothew's course of action, which broke the causal link.|$|R
